description.narrative:
At the individual level, LP aims at healing the Trauma of Individual men, ensuring that men heal from conflict and violence-related trauma in ways that are specific to their gender identities and that take into account gendered coping mechanisms. For the year 2020-2021, 198 LP psychosocial support group sessions have been implemented from February to September 2021, to directly reach 2970 men and their spouses in different community located in North and South Kivu as well as Ituri Province (see the distribution of participants per targeted groups).
• 330 men have been reached in 22 groups psychosocial groups of husbands of women survivors of
SGBV;
• 660 men have been reached in 44 LP groups of the military men (22 in North and 22 in South Kivu);
• 660 Men have been reached in 44 LP groups of the Police (22 in North and 22 South Kivu);
• 330 Men have been reached in 22 LP groups with Men Ex-Combatants;
• 990 Men have been reached in 66 LP Groups in high-risk zones (22 in North Kivu, 22 in the South Kivu and 22 in Ituri province.
